1 packet Crispy Shallots
280 g Salmon
1 packet Sriracha
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Slaw Mix
1 packet Basmati Rice
1 packet Ponzu Sauce
1 sachet Sesame Seeds
1 White Turnip
1 packet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 drizzle olive oil
1.5 cup water (for the rice)

• To a medium saucepan, add the water and bring to the boil.
• Add basmati rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low.
• Cook for 10 minutes, then remove pan from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don’t peek!

• While rice is cooking, roughly chop baby leaves. Thinly slice white turnip.
• Spread sesame seeds over a plate. Pat salmon dry with paper towel.
• In a medium bowl, combine salmon, sweet soy seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt.
• Press salmon, skin-side down, into sesame seeds to coat.

• When the rice has 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan with a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side (depending on thickness). Transfer to a plate to rest.
• Meanwhile, combine sriracha, the honey and a splash of water in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine baby spinach, slaw mix, turnip, ponzu sauce (see ingredients) and a drizzle of sesame oil and vinegar. Season to taste.
• Divide basmati rice between bowls. Top with sesame salmon and ponzu slaw. Drizzle over honey sriracha sauce.
• Garnish with crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy